content.name: Spore Sword
content.itemDescription: A short sword with poisonous abilities when transformed. Each attack throws two spores and envenoms every enemy that hits the wielder.

content.name: Morning Star
content.itemDescription: A knight's morning star is so heavy it is carried as a Big Sword. When transformed its weight can provoke a low-intensity seism in the room.

content.name: Ghost Gloves
content.itemDescription: Ghostly gloves able to contact enemies despite not being tangible. When transformed they are able to create spiritual projectiles.

content.name: Thief Gauntlet
content.itemDescription: Famous type of gloves beloved by robbers. When transformed they make enemies drop items in exchange of users health.

content.name: Gas Spear
content.itemDescription: A poisonous spear filled with a toxic liquid. When transformed it expels toxic gas that envenoms enemies.

content.name: Bone Sword
content.itemDescription: A short sword made out of bones. When transformed, its speed and damage are increased.

content.name: Composite Bow
content.itemDescription: Due to the flexible and light materials of this bow its shooting speed increases when transformed.

content.name: Staff Spear
content.itemDescription: A fire staff from a magical dimension. When transformed it is able to cast fire balls from its tip.

content.name: Explosive Bow
content.itemDescription: High tech bow that adds to each arrow an explosive head when transformed.

content.name: Training Short Sword
content.itemDescription: With sword in hand and shield in the other, this combination strikes a perfect balance between attack and defense.

content.name: Training Big Sword
content.itemDescription: It's a big sword. Large attack area, but it isn't very sharp. You are basically swinging an oversized metal bat with this equipped.

content.name: Training Spear
content.itemDescription: The spear is the longest ranged melee weapon one could wield. Easy to fling around, but difficult to master.

content.name: Training Bow
content.itemDescription: Wood and metal from the Golem culture merge harmoniously to create a well-balanced bow.

content.name: Training Gloves
content.itemDescription: Incredibly light, incredibly fast, incredibly satisfying. Due to their short range though, they are much riskier than other weapons.

content.name: Broom Spear
content.itemDescription: A tool with one, simple purpose. To clean. At least, that is if held in untrained hands.

content.name: Rough Gloves
content.itemDescription: May Stun. These are not so much gloves, but small boulders crudely attached to your hands.

content.name: Soldier Short Sword
content.itemDescription: The best materials of the Golem culture polished to a fault.

content.name: Rusty Short Sword
content.itemDescription: May Stun. Why cut when you can bash. At least.... that is the thought with this one.

content.name: Buster Big Sword
content.itemDescription: This greatsword is the result of countless hours of polishing the blade using the unique rocks and water of the Golem Dungeon.

content.name: Warrior Spear
content.itemDescription: A mighty spear built with the strength required to shape Golems.

content.name: Golem Drill Spear
content.itemDescription: May Stun. Intended for mining, the spear head was made incredibly hard to pierce through rock. This principle applies to most enemies.

content.name: Catapult Bow
content.itemDescription: May Stun. I mean... This thing comprise of random resources from the Golem Dungeon is essentially chunking rocks.

content.name: Rock Big Sword
content.itemDescription: May Stun. Really, they decided to throw out the idea of a sword cutting with this one. Designed to purely crush your foes.

content.name: Steel Boots
content.itemDescription: Offer resounding protection. Which is good, because one is not going to be dodging musch with this much metal strapped to their feet.

content.name: Iron Boots
content.itemDescription: Originally mass produced for soldiers of the Grand Army, but works equally well for anyone Dungeon diving.

content.name: Fabric Boots
content.itemDescription: Boots made out of resilient fabric. Perfect for travelers, but not the best at protecting feet from enemy attacks.

content.name: Steel Chestplate
content.itemDescription: Chestplate offering the best protection against enemies. It's incredibly heavy though. Basically a chunk of steel strapped to ones chest.

content.name: Iron Chestplate
content.itemDescription: Basic armor most commonly used by Merchants. Fairly light with decent resistance and mobility.

content.name: Fabric Chestplate
content.itemDescription: The sturdy fabric of this tunic is durable while remaining light.

content.name: Steel Helmet
content.itemDescription: Layers of the heaviest, thickest metals crafted into a sturdy, resilient, damage reducing helmet.

content.name: Iron Helmet
content.itemDescription: Headgear made from the lightest metals available. It's a trade off between armor and agility.

content.name: Fabric Bandana
content.itemDescription: This semi-ordinary bandana is weaved together with the strongest fibers to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Hero's Bow
content.itemDescription: Strange ancient bow made from materials that can't be found in this world.

content.name: Hero's Sword
content.itemDescription: Old sword said to have been carried by a legendary hero.

content.name: Hunter Bow
content.itemDescription: Wood and metal from the Golem culture merge harmoniously to create a well-balanced bow.

content.name: Fighter Gloves
content.itemDescription: Let us be honest for a moment. These are just giant claws made of Golem Iron. As equally ferocious as they are crude.

content.name: Ragnarok Big Sword
content.itemDescription: Big sword with so much strength in it that it is said to bring the end of the world.

content.name: Ether Sable
content.itemDescription: Sword with a blade made by manipulating photons. Its design is owned by a dimensional militia.

content.name: Valkyrie Spear
content.itemDescription: Spear carried by mighty female warriors in other dimension known for their skill at combat.

content.name: Master Fists
content.itemDescription: The best design for a pair of gloves. Brought from a dimension where a famous contact warrior created them.

content.name: Runic Bow
content.itemDescription: Bow full of runes allowing it to create mortal immaterial arrows.

content.name: Composite Armor Boots
content.itemDescription: This sci-fi looking bandana is composed of the strongest materials known by the ICT to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Composite Armor Helmet
content.itemDescription: This sci-fi looking bandana is composed of the strongest materials known by the ICT to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Composite Armor Chestplate
content.itemDescription: This sci-fi looking chestplate is composed of the strongest materials known by the ITC to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Forest Spirit Gloves
content.itemDescription: Vines covered in thorns wrapped around one's hand to symbolize the simple death nature itself can provide.

content.name: Venom Twins Gloves
content.itemDescription: Poisons. Small bags of poison residing inside the gloves inject a small dose of poison directly into your foes.

content.name: Knight Short Sword
content.itemDescription: Superior metals of the Golem culture fuse with exquisite wood of the Forest culture to create this elaborate piece of equipment.

content.name: Venom Short Sword
content.itemDescription: Poisons. From the hilt, poison seeps down the blade to inflict lasting pain upon one's foes.

content.name: Wild Big Sword
content.itemDescription: I remember comparing that training sword to a baseball bat... this is truly a giant baseball bat.

content.name: Toxic Big Sword
content.itemDescription: Poisons. Forged by injecting the poisoned fluids of the Forest Dungeon directly into the wood.

content.name: Wood's Spear
content.itemDescription: Built strong, but incredibly flexible. Beautifully crafted from wood found from the Forest culture.

content.name: Venom Sting Spear
content.itemDescription: Poisons. A simplistic wooden spear, but poison running through the shaft into the spearhead will leave anyone in pain.

content.name: Natural Bow
content.itemDescription: The fiber based resources of the Forest culture come together here to create a remarkably light, yet powerful bow.

content.name: Poison Bow
content.itemDescription: Poisons. Upon knocking an arrow, it becomes poisoned via the venomous bowstring. Requires special care when using.

content.name: Composite Armor Chestplate II
content.itemDescription: This sci-fi looking chestplate is composed of the strongest materials known by the ITC to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Composite Armor Boots II
content.itemDescription: This sci-fi looking bandana is composed of the strongest materials known by the ICT to help protect the wearer.

content.name: Captain Gloves
content.itemDescription: Special alloy metals and an experimental smelting process makes these gloves stronger than most without adding unnecessary weight.

content.name: Flame Gloves
content.itemDescription: Burns. The magnetic cores embedded in these gloves keep lava constantly flowing even while punching.

content.name: Commander Short Sword
content.itemDescription: Casting from the lava of the Desert culture creates a powerful sword and shield to the standard of any commander worth their salt.

content.name: Reborn Short Sword
content.itemDescription: Burns. The flames of the forge never left this sword, the heat of the desert still radiating from the blade.

content.name: Vulcan Big Sword
content.itemDescription: One of the heaviest greatswords to come out of Rynoka. Forged from Desert Steel, it is an unstoppable, wrecking machine.

content.name: Blaze Big Sword
content.itemDescription: Burns. Must be the combination of lava infused directly into the metal.

content.name: Monkey Spear
content.itemDescription: The tale of the Monkey King comes to mind as one looks upon this crimson spear. Truly a spear worthy of him.

content.name: Hell Spear
content.itemDescription: Burns. The three desert suns reflect off of the shaft of this spear, directing high temperatures into the spear head.

content.name: Soldier Bow
content.itemDescription: Crudely crafted from the limited fibers of the Desert culture, this bow looks best in the hands of a soldier. Regardless, it gets the job done.

content.name: Flamethrower Bow
content.itemDescription: Burns. Lava flowing through the bow's core superheats the arrows, lighting them on fire.
